attachments.title: Hear The Debut Single From EL VY, The New Project From The National’s Matt Berninger & Menomena’s Brent Knopf - Stereogum
attachments.text: The National's Matt Berninger and Ramona Falls/Menomena's Brent Knopf have teamed up under the name EL VY. (Oddly enough, this marks the second National/Menomena partnership after Bryan Devendorf and Danny Seim joined forces as Pfarmers last year.) EL VY's debut album, Return To The Moon, is out later this year on 4AD, and today they've shared the title track. "Return To The Moon" -- which bears the curious subtitle "(Political Song For Didi Bloome To Sing, With Crescendo)" -- pits Berninger's unmistakably weary baritone against brighter, funkier music than we've come to expect. It's still spiked with that familiar melancholy, though; it strikes me as an alternate-dimension version of Alligator-era National, "Secret Meeting" in particular. Watch a lyric video below, where you can also see the album's tracklist and EL VY's world tour dates.
